Package: aucmat
Title: Scalable and Statistically Principled ROC Analysis for High-Dimensional Biomarker Matrices
Version: 0.2.0
Date: 2026-07-22
Authors@R:
    person("Lucas", "VHH Tran", email = "lucas.tran@ck-care.ch", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Matrix-first ROC analysis for high-dimensional molecular biomarker data.
    Provides fast, direction-preserving AUC estimation over biomarker matrices with DeLong
    and stratified-bootstrap inference, multiplicity adjustment, paired comparisons on
    common subjects, and bootstrap rank-stability analysis. Designed for univariate
    screening and ranking of genes, proteins, and metabolites measured on the same subjects.
